9.14.19  2:16 pm   Any tips when it comes to producing and mixing music? What were some of the problems you've encountered over all these years, and how did you overcome them?

      a big tip i didn't expect, but found very useful, is watch out for very low frequencies coming from not-bass , not-kick, not-supposed-to-be-bass instruments. like the chords/pianos/guitars. clean that up, and the whole house feels cleaner. also don't forget the lyrics

9.14.19  11:58 am   i just realized the keyboard i'm borrowing to use for a production of mamma mia (musical comprised of ABBA songs if you didn't know) is the same keyboard you use, the mx61.

     don't have that one yet, i still have the previous model

      any tasty synth sounds or other sounds you particularly like on there? 

     i only use the 74 rhodes, and the advantage of the older version is they have vibrado preset on the mod wheel (strangely, but that's a good thing i found). mx61 apparently does not do that out of the box, and with that sound you wanna make sure you go mono because the panLR gets old. besides that it's all midi usage, for me. i doubt you'll find too many great sounds inside. that's why it's so insanely insanely light weight, which is probably my favorite feature. good for juggling the instrument
